9. Game Character HAS Weapons (Composition + Behavior Changing)
ğŸ¯ Goal:
Show how composition allows behavior to change at runtime (switching weapons).

A Character HAS a Weapon.

ğŸªœ Detailed Step-by-Step Instructions:
Create a Weapon class

Instance variables:

name (String)

damage (int)

Constructor to set these.

Method:

public void use() {
    System.out.println("Attacking with " + name + " (Damage: " + damage + ")");
}
Create a Character class

Instance variables:

name

Weapon weapon (This is Composition)

Constructor sets both.

Create method:

public void attack() {
    System.out.println(name + " is attacking!");
    weapon.use();
}
In main()

Create a Character with a Sword weapon.

Call attack().

Change the weapon to a Bow.

Call attack() again.

âœ… Expected Output:
Knight is attacking!
Attacking with Sword (Damage: 50)
Knight is attacking!
Attacking with Bow (Damage: 30)



